Australia Beat England to Lead Field Hockey Series 2-0 
Australia scored their second win over England to gain a 2-0 lead in
the six-test series of internalional hockey series in Adelaide of
Australia on Saturday.
Australia, bronze medallists at last year's World Cup in Sydney, beat
the England side 3-1 after led 2-0 at half-time.
Paul Lewis opened the scoring in the 13th minute while Jay Stacey
scored in the 30th and 58th minutes.
England pulled back to 2-1 early in the second half with a goal from
Jason Lee.
The third match in the series will be played here on Monday.
